<h3>Key Patterns Across All Studies</h3>
<p>Three patterns hold true regardless of which study you reference:</p>
<p><strong>1. Position 1 captures disproportionate traffic.</strong> The gap between position 1 and position 2 is the largest gap on the page. Position 1 gets 1.7x to 2.1x more clicks than position 2.</p>
<p><strong>2. CTR drops sharply after position 3.</strong> Positions 1-3 collectively capture 55-70% of all clicks. Positions 4-10 split the remaining 30-45%.</p>
<p><strong>3. Page 2 is effectively invisible.</strong> Position 11+ gets under 1% CTR. <a href="https://ahrefs.com/blog/seo-statistics/">96.55% of all pages get zero organic traffic</a>, and ranking on page 2 is a major reason why.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>The practical takeaway: moving from position 4 to position 1 can triple your traffic. Moving from position 11 to position 10 delivers almost nothing. Focus your efforts on queries where you are already on page 1.</p>
</blockquote>
